I have something that I want to get off my chest about RECRUITERS....

You are some of the hardest working folks I’ve ever met. I have worked with many of you over the last few months and I have learned one thing. You have a tremendously difficult job that goes a mile a minute. You are probably chasing down a dozen reqs at once, juggling 20 or more phone calls a day, scheduling interviews, and getting feedback to/from everybody.

The amount of organization it takes to do all of this is incredible and I know the job rarely ends when you leave work for the day. I for one appreciate everything you put into matching people to a job where they will feel fulfilled and really make a difference.
Please like this post if you agree and send me a friend request. I'd love to link up with some great recruiters.
1. What is your current compensation ? - "My target compensation is X"
2. Can you provide your salary history ? - "My target compensation is X"
3. What was your last pay rise ? - "My target compensation is X"
4. What is the lowest offer you would accept ? - "My target compensation is X"
One smart answer to 4 stupid questions: "My target compensation is X"
Good recruiters do not ask these questions above.
1. "Based on your resume, I have 3 openings that you may be interested in. Quickly about each <..> Which ones interest you most" ?
2. "What would you like to know about the job, the hiring manager, the team, the company, the culture, the compensation and benefits ?"
3. "Based on your resume here is what I plan to tell the hiring manager about you. <...> Do you have anything to add  ?"
These questions show that the recruiter has done the homework on you and the companies, and is not wasting anyone's time, including their own.
These recruiters will find you the job you are looking for.
